It seems that I made an error in the XML structure. Here is a revised version of the mission plan with the correct XML structure:
```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<MissionPlan>
  <CompositeTaskInformation>
    <TaskDescription>
      <Action>DriveToTree</Action>
      <Arguments>
        <Argument name="treeId">1</Argument>
      </Arguments>
      <Outcome>
        <DrivingDistance>0.25 km</DrivingDistance>
        <GPSLocation>-120.42309252722157, 37.36631509745154</GPSLocation>
      </Outcome>
    </TaskDescription>
    <TaskDescription>
      <Action>TakePictureOfTree</Action>
      <Arguments>
        <Argument name="treeId">1</Argument>
      </Arguments>
      <Condition>
        <Temperature below="33.0째C"/>
      </Condition>
      <Outcome>
        <GPSLocation>-120.42309252722157, 37.36631509745154</GPSLocation>
      </Outcome>
    </TaskDescription>
    <TaskDescription>
      <Action>TakeCo2Sample</Action>
      <Arguments>
        <Argument name="treeId">1</Argument>
      </Arguments>
      <Condition>
        <Temperature below="33.0째C"/>
      </Condition>
      <Outcome>
        <GPSLocation>-120.42309252722157, 37.36631509745154</GPSLocation>
      </Outcome>
    </TaskDescription>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>
  
  <CompositeTaskInformation>
    <TaskDescription>
      <Action>DriveToTree</Action>
      <Arguments>
        <Argument name="treeId">6</Argument>
      </Arguments>
      <Outcome>
        <DrivingDistance>0.30 km</DrivingDistance>
        <GPSLocation>-120.42306783300766, 37.366308661662266</GPSLocation>
      </Outcome>
    </TaskDescription>
    <TaskDescription>
      <Action>TakePictureOfTree</Action>
      <Arguments>
        <Argument name="treeId">6</Argument>
      </Arguments>
      <Condition>
        <Temperature below="33.0째C"/>
      </Condition>
      <Outcome>
        <GPSLocation>-120.42306783300766, 37.366308661662266</GPSLocation>
      </Outcome>
    </TaskDescription>
    <TaskDescription>
      <Action>TakeCo2Sample</Action>
      <Arguments>
        <Argument name="treeId">6</Argument>
      </Arguments>
      <Condition>
        <Temperature below="33.0째C"/>
      </Condition>
      <Outcome>
        <GPSLocation>-120.42306783300766, 37.366308661662266</GPSLocation>
      </Outcome>
    </TaskDescription>
  </CompositeTaskInformation>
  
  <StartSequence>
    <TaskReference task="DriveToTree_1"/>
    <TaskReference task="TakePictureOfTree_1"/>
    <TaskReference task="TakeCo2Sample_1"/>
    
    <TaskReference task="DriveToTree_6"/>
    <TaskReference task="TakePictureOfTree_6"/>
    <TaskReference task="TakeCo2Sample_6"/>
  </StartSequence>
</MissionPlan>
```
I added a `StartSequence` element to define the sequence of tasks that should be executed first. I also wrapped each `TaskDescription` in a separate `CompositeTaskInformation` element.

Please note that this is just one possible way to structure your mission plan, and you may need to adjust it to fit your specific requirements.